  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to see a different status for messages sent when I was offline so I can know that they are not sent yet.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n*Summary*: It's not true that a message is sent when device is offline. Maybe \"Sent\" status should be changed to \"Sending..\".\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nI understand that some of my messages have not been sent yet.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nEven if I send a message when I'm offline the status is \"Sent\".\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Go to a chat\r\n- Turn airplane mode\r\n- Send a message. Message status is \"Sent\"\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, March 1\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS",
